        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Control Loop Programming</strong></p><p>You just adopted Charles the gecko, and you want to keep it healthy! Charles&#x27;s terrarium has a heat lamp, a fan, and a humidifier. The program below controls these devices to change the temperature and humidity. Copy these questions into your workspace and figure out how to set up a self-maintaining environment for Charles.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "yYnPi_2Ln9saLJbv",
        "title": "Ideal Gecko Conditions",
        "content": {
          "type": "Question",
          "version": 1,
          "locked": false,
          "questionId": "2_m1gg",
          "tiles": [
            {
              "id": "imx1rD6GNo2OOhop",
              "title": "Question Prompt",
              "fixedPosition": true,
              "content": {
                "type": "Text",
                "format": "html",
                "text": [
                  "<p>What strategy can you use to figure out the optimal conditions for Charles? Hint, a happy gecko is a lively gecko. When the conditions are wrong he&#x27;s listless and still.  </p>"
                ]
              }
            },
            [
              {
                "id": "elU0T295Apb4Xcu0",
                "title": "Gecko love",
                "content": {
                  "type": "Simulator",
                  "simulation": "terrarium"
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "1FR8Xc4mVFf0oAut",
                "title": "Text 3",
                "content": {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "format": "html",
                  "text": [
                    "<p>Discuss strategies to identify how Charles likes his terrarium.</p>"
                  ]
                }
              }
            ]
          ]
        }
